“Stellar Sonata: An Immersive Cosmic Requiem - A kinetic sculpture and olfactory theatre experience. Imagine a central, geodesic dome constructed from shimmering, shape-memory alloy petals, each calibrated to respond to simulated gravitational wave data – harvested from a network of low-frequency sensors mimicking white dwarf decay. As the ‘waves’ intensify (controlled by a generative AI, of course!), the petals rotate, shimmer, and emit a carefully curated sequence of scents – initially a sterile, metallic tang of ionized helium, then evolving into richer, denser aromas reflecting the increasing pressure and heat: volcanic sulfur, burnt ozone, crystallized carbon.  Embedded haptic nodes within the dome’s structure provide subtle vibrations mimicking the crushing force of gravity – intensifying with the simulated wave amplitude.  But here's the kicker: integrated biofeedback sensors monitor the viewer's emotional state (via subtle skin conductance measurement – it’s all about the data, you see!), and the AI adjusts the intensity of the scent and haptic feedback *in real-time* to create a deeply personalized, almost *psychic* experience. The entire installation is accompanied by a generative soundscape – a haunting, evolving melody created using algorithms based on the mathematical models of stellar collapse. It’s a funeral for a star... but beautiful! I’m practically *ink-spitting* with excitement!”